properties.headline: FLOODING - CARRATHOOL SHIRE COUNCIL Various roads
properties.otherAdvice:
Some roads in the Carrathool Shire are affected by flooding:

Road closures are only updated during Council office hours - Monday to Friday 8:30am to 4:15pm. For updates after hours, please call 0407 244 429 or check council's website.

properties.otherAdvice:
Flooding has washed away the bridge over Billys creek. 
Expected to remain closed until further notice.

properties.headline: FLOODING - ALBION PARK RAIL Illawarra Highway between Princes Highway AND Tongarra Road, Albion Park
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice: Traffic control will be in place due to water and debris still affecting sections of the road.

properties.headline: FLOODING - MACQUARIE PASS Illawarra Highway between Robertson and Albion Park
properties.otherAdvice:
This closure will remain in place until further notice.

Residents only may be permitted past closure points, at the discretion of emergency services.
properties.diversions:
Motorists are advised to use Picton Rd and Princes Motorway as an alternative route.

Light vehicles can also use Jamberoo Mountain Road.
